WEBVTT

00:03.938 --> 00:05.539
[phone ringing]

00:05.539 --> 00:07.507
[munching chips]

00:08.842 --> 00:11.077
- [door opens]
- [indistinct chatter]

00:16.483 --> 00:18.452
All right, Goddamn it.

00:18.452 --> 00:20.754
- I'm gonna get
to the bottom of this.
- [Bear] I'm not...

00:20.754 --> 00:23.724
I-I mean, I-I...
I don't...

00:23.724 --> 00:26.227
Uh, I mean... I, uh, uh...

00:26.227 --> 00:27.628
I mean, I-I, uh...

00:27.628 --> 00:29.296
- I mean--
- What?

00:29.296 --> 00:31.198
This is so stressful.

00:31.198 --> 00:33.534
Aw. You want some cookies
and milk?

00:33.534 --> 00:36.102
I'd-I'd love some.

00:37.537 --> 00:39.106
You're gonna talk to me.

00:39.106 --> 00:40.607
- [gulps]
- You hear me?

00:41.842 --> 00:44.411
I see you.

00:44.411 --> 00:47.147
Man, I ain't got
to say shit to you.

00:47.147 --> 00:48.749
This Indian land.

00:48.749 --> 00:51.351
I want a lawyer and my grandma.

00:56.189 --> 00:57.524
[White Steve]
<i>If you need me</i>

00:57.524 --> 01:01.095
to wear a wire... I will.

01:01.095 --> 01:03.397
- None of this was my idea.
- [Elora] <i>Big,</i>

01:03.397 --> 01:04.764
you know I'm not
telling you shit.

01:05.732 --> 01:07.767
♪ ♪

01:13.640 --> 01:17.077
Fuck it. It all started
at Elder Breakfast.

01:17.077 --> 01:19.145
[indistinct chatter]

01:22.449 --> 01:24.418
Auntie, hook it up
with extra fry bread.

01:24.418 --> 01:27.354
You're not even an elder.
You should be serving me.

01:27.354 --> 01:29.757
I know, but...

01:29.757 --> 01:31.692
I'm on sacred duties right now.

01:31.692 --> 01:33.493
I'm Fixico's plus-one.

01:34.661 --> 01:37.298
[Big]
<i>And what the fuck you doing
at the Elders Breakfast?</i>

01:37.298 --> 01:39.366
<i>Mvto.</i>

01:39.366 --> 01:41.602
'Cause Fixico's been
teaching me his wizard ways.

01:41.602 --> 01:44.071
Most time, we just
hang out at the clinic

01:44.071 --> 01:46.073
and go deliver groceries
and shit.

01:46.073 --> 01:48.208
I didn't learn any spells yet,

01:48.208 --> 01:50.444
but I wasn't sure
if it was, like,

01:50.444 --> 01:52.780
a wax on, wax off situation.

01:52.780 --> 01:55.382
Know what I mean? So,

01:55.382 --> 01:58.418
I just shut the fuck about it
and just went with it.

02:03.123 --> 02:05.526
Ah, there she is.

02:05.526 --> 02:07.027
My protégé.

02:07.027 --> 02:08.729
[Wotko]
Oh, okay, how's it going?

02:08.729 --> 02:10.664
This guy teaching you the ways?

02:10.664 --> 02:12.499
[Willie Jack]
Yeah. It's been good.

02:12.499 --> 02:15.169
Mostly just sitting around
all the time.

02:15.169 --> 02:16.604
[laughter]

02:16.604 --> 02:19.440
Yeah, he's good at that.
[laughs]

02:19.440 --> 02:21.642
I'm not young anymore like you.

02:21.642 --> 02:24.578
- I need to sit.
- Understandable.

02:24.578 --> 02:26.413
Should have seen him
back in the old days.

02:26.413 --> 02:29.250
Boy, he always drove
these keen cars.

02:29.250 --> 02:30.684
- Keen car.
- [Wotko] Crazy women.

02:30.684 --> 02:32.152
- Mm.
- [Willie Jack] Oh!
- [laughter]

02:33.487 --> 02:35.589
The good old days, huh?

02:35.589 --> 02:37.624
- Boarding school life,
huh? Yeah.
- [Wotko] Mm-hmm.

02:38.625 --> 02:39.793
Me and Irene--

02:39.793 --> 02:42.363
[Irene]
Bucky, Brownie...

02:42.363 --> 02:45.032
- and Mabel.
- [Fixico] Oh, yeah,

02:45.032 --> 02:46.767
- good ol' Mabel. Yeah.
- [Irene] Mm-hmm.

02:46.767 --> 02:49.469
Let's not forget about Chibon.

02:52.172 --> 02:55.109
Yes. Chibon.

02:55.109 --> 02:56.443
Who dat?

02:56.443 --> 02:58.345
It's my brother-cousin.

02:58.345 --> 03:00.481
Oh.

03:00.481 --> 03:02.683
He pass away?

03:02.683 --> 03:06.420
No. He's still out there.

03:06.420 --> 03:08.222
[Wotko]
Mm-hmm.

03:08.222 --> 03:10.124
I always thought
we'd make amends

03:10.124 --> 03:12.226
before one of us left.

03:12.226 --> 03:14.295
Why don't you just
go talk to him?

03:14.295 --> 03:16.430
It's complicated.

03:16.430 --> 03:20.134
By "complicated," he just means
he's an Indian man,

03:20.134 --> 03:21.769
- you know?
- Mm.

03:21.769 --> 03:23.270
- [laughter]
- [Irene] <i>Ennit?</i>

03:23.270 --> 03:25.773
- Maybe he just needs an invite.
- Ah.

03:25.773 --> 03:27.775
You don't know Chibon.

03:27.775 --> 03:30.344
Mean son of a bitch.

03:30.344 --> 03:32.279
[mouthing]

03:32.279 --> 03:34.247
Yeah.

03:35.816 --> 03:37.284
[Willie Jack]
Mm.

04:06.313 --> 04:08.048
- [Fixico coughs]
- [thud]

04:08.048 --> 04:10.050
- [people gasp]
- [man] Call 911!

04:11.852 --> 04:14.688
[Big]
I know Fixico had
a heart attack,

04:14.688 --> 04:17.390
but where the bus come in at?

04:18.392 --> 04:20.260
We needed wheels.

04:21.061 --> 04:23.297
[Kenny Boy]
So, let me get this straight.

04:23.297 --> 04:25.432
Here you are again,

04:25.432 --> 04:27.701
borrowing another car

04:27.701 --> 04:30.404
from yours truly.

04:30.404 --> 04:32.206
And you want to borrow it

04:32.206 --> 04:35.542
so you can kidnap
a distant uncle-cousin

04:35.542 --> 04:38.045
that's a mental patient

04:38.045 --> 04:40.480
in a hospital in Tulsa?

04:42.082 --> 04:43.317
Yeah.

04:43.317 --> 04:46.687
Which I have to tell you
is a bad idea.

04:46.687 --> 04:48.822
You don't take 'em
out of the hospital.

04:48.822 --> 04:50.824
It never ends good.
They usually kill someone.

04:50.824 --> 04:52.526
So, just keep that in mind.

04:52.526 --> 04:54.661
Okay? [sighs]

04:55.462 --> 04:58.332
You expect me to just
give you a car and be on my way?

04:58.332 --> 04:59.700
- Yeah.
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

04:59.700 --> 05:01.101
- Yeah, pretty much, yeah.
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm-hmm.

05:01.101 --> 05:02.436
- Yeah.
- [Cheese clears throat]

05:02.436 --> 05:06.240
Okay.
I have some stipulations.

05:06.240 --> 05:08.309
[sighs]
Of course.

05:08.309 --> 05:10.678
[Kenny Boy]
[sighs] Number one.

05:10.678 --> 05:13.079
You're gonna need more
than a car.

05:15.082 --> 05:17.117
They needed professionals.

05:17.117 --> 05:19.153
The fuck's all over your face?

05:19.153 --> 05:20.321
[soft chuckle]

05:20.321 --> 05:21.488
<i>Now, second.</i>

05:21.488 --> 05:24.457
I am no longer Kenny Boy.

05:26.059 --> 05:28.062
I'm Uncle.

05:28.062 --> 05:29.563
Uncle Kenny,

05:29.563 --> 05:31.232
Uncle Ken.

05:31.232 --> 05:34.335
Uncle Boy, Uncle KK.

05:34.335 --> 05:36.570
KK. Two Ks, never three.
Three's bad.

05:36.570 --> 05:39.273
All right, everybody say it.

05:39.273 --> 05:41.642
- Uncle Boy.
- Uncle Kenny.
- Uncle.

05:41.642 --> 05:44.111
Uncle.

05:44.111 --> 05:45.613
Not you.

05:45.613 --> 05:47.114
Sorry.

05:47.114 --> 05:48.515
One more time.

05:48.515 --> 05:50.351
- [all] Uncle Boy.
- Uncle.

05:50.351 --> 05:53.353
Ah. Nice.

05:58.292 --> 06:00.127
Welcome aboard, kids.

06:00.127 --> 06:02.029
[Ansel]
One, two.

06:02.029 --> 06:03.631
[Kenny Boy]
This is a school bus.

06:03.631 --> 06:05.766
I'm sure none of you have ever
gotten on one of these.

06:05.766 --> 06:08.369
[Ansel]
Three, four.

06:08.369 --> 06:11.238
Five. Seven.

06:11.238 --> 06:15.376
Six. Seven. Eight.

06:15.376 --> 06:17.177
Count of four.

06:17.177 --> 06:18.779
<i>♪ But I can't see... ♪</i>

06:18.779 --> 06:20.781
[hooting]

06:20.781 --> 06:22.816
[Elora]
Oh, hell, no.

06:22.816 --> 06:24.718
Now let's go find
this mentalist.

06:24.718 --> 06:26.320
Buckle up.

06:26.320 --> 06:27.655
- There's-there's...
- There's no seatbelts.

06:27.655 --> 06:29.290
- No seatbelts.
- No seatbelts.

06:29.290 --> 06:31.157
Then hold on to the seats.

06:32.159 --> 06:33.527
It's gonna get rough.

06:33.527 --> 06:35.496
Bunch of babies.

06:35.496 --> 06:37.298
<i>♪ Please just forget about me ♪</i>

06:37.298 --> 06:38.766
<i>♪ Cancel out my name... ♪</i>

06:38.766 --> 06:40.434
[Kenny Boy hooting]

06:40.434 --> 06:42.502
[engine sputters]

06:44.338 --> 06:46.740
<i>♪ Don't get angry with me. ♪</i>

06:55.482 --> 06:57.117
[Ansel sniffing]

06:58.652 --> 07:00.054
What's your name?

07:00.054 --> 07:02.522
Bone Thug Dog.

07:03.523 --> 07:05.292
Bone Thug Dog?

07:06.660 --> 07:09.763
That's a beautiful name.

07:14.401 --> 07:16.704
[Cheese]
Originally, it was <i>Gojira.</i>

07:16.704 --> 07:19.240
In 1956, when they were
bringing it over to the States,

07:19.240 --> 07:21.575
they translated <i>Gojira</i>
to <i>Godzilla.</i>

07:21.575 --> 07:24.111
See...

07:24.111 --> 07:25.512
- [White Steve] Wow.
- [Cheese] Mm-hmm.

07:25.512 --> 07:27.281
Fuck off.

07:27.281 --> 07:28.816
What are you doing?

07:28.816 --> 07:30.650
What?

07:36.556 --> 07:39.126
Hey.

07:39.126 --> 07:41.194
'Sup?

07:43.063 --> 07:46.566
I just wanted you to know
that I'm proud of you.

07:47.567 --> 07:50.604
Oh. Okay.

07:50.604 --> 07:52.473
Thanks, bro.

07:52.473 --> 07:55.643
Yeah, I mean, usually,
we're stealing copper

07:55.643 --> 07:59.046
or steaks for cookouts
or edibles,

07:59.046 --> 08:01.582
but this feels...

08:01.582 --> 08:04.117
meaningful, I guess.

08:06.153 --> 08:09.522
Yeah, I guess you're right.
It is meaningful.

08:11.758 --> 08:13.994
You worried about Fixico?

08:15.796 --> 08:19.699
Feels like I didn't get
to spend enough time with him.

08:22.669 --> 08:25.306
That how I felt
when Grandma died.

08:25.306 --> 08:28.442
Just thinking about

08:28.442 --> 08:30.311
her sitting in the living room,

08:30.311 --> 08:32.746
drinking coffee,
reading the paper,

08:32.746 --> 08:34.782
watching TV.

08:34.782 --> 08:38.018
Could've just sat with her.

08:40.554 --> 08:42.355
I didn't.

08:43.523 --> 08:45.492
That's why I think it's good

08:45.492 --> 08:47.494
to keep our elders around.

08:47.494 --> 08:50.431
We're always
learning stuff from them,

08:50.431 --> 08:52.233
no matter what,

08:52.233 --> 08:54.334
even if we're just
sitting there.

08:56.303 --> 08:57.571
Wizard ways.

08:57.571 --> 08:59.239
Hmm.

09:01.208 --> 09:04.144
If you go first, bro,
I'll be by your side.

09:05.112 --> 09:07.214
Dark.

09:07.214 --> 09:09.282
It's true, though.

09:10.684 --> 09:13.720
If you go first,
I'll be by yours.

09:14.721 --> 09:16.523
I mean that.

09:16.523 --> 09:18.558
Love you, bro.

09:21.528 --> 09:23.997
Hey, you guys, look.
They're hugging!

09:28.068 --> 09:29.403
I don't care, either.

09:29.403 --> 09:31.538
Welcome to Tulsa, kids.

09:31.538 --> 09:34.775
Home of Leon Russell,
Gary Busey,

09:34.775 --> 09:37.478
<i>The Outsiders, Rumble Fish,</i>

09:37.478 --> 09:40.314
and American classic <i>UHF.</i>

09:40.314 --> 09:42.249
- [bus brakes squeak]
- [indistinct chatter]

09:42.249 --> 09:44.285
All right, shitasses.

09:44.285 --> 09:46.687
Cheese stayed up all night
doing this, so, thanks, Cheese.

09:46.687 --> 09:48.222
No need to thank me.

09:48.222 --> 09:49.723
- What is it?
- [Bear] It is...

09:49.723 --> 09:51.759
- a layout to the hospital.
- Oh.

09:51.759 --> 09:54.028
- [Kenny Boy] Nice.
- Good shit, bro.
- Yes.

09:54.028 --> 09:55.329
- That's nice.
- [Cheese] Thanks.

09:55.329 --> 09:57.464
It... it was-it was easy.
You know, uh,

09:57.464 --> 10:00.634
just googled "behavior health
hospitals" and found this.

10:00.634 --> 10:03.070
Williams Memorial Hospital.
Yeah. One quick deep dive later,

10:03.070 --> 10:05.172
I found the schematics.
I didn't have a printer,

10:05.172 --> 10:07.541
- so I just drew it myself.
- [Bear] Drew it, man.

10:07.541 --> 10:10.511
- [overlapping chatter]
- Nice, bro. I didn't know you
was deadly like that.

10:10.511 --> 10:12.646
- [Cheese] It's cool, man.
- Wait, bro.
Williams Memorial Hospital?

10:12.646 --> 10:14.548
- Yeah.
- This ain't Williams Memorial.

10:14.548 --> 10:16.250
This is Johnson Memorial.

10:16.250 --> 10:18.218
Shit. Is it?

10:18.218 --> 10:20.354
- [Bone Thug Dog] Aw, fuck, man.
- [Weeze] Shit.

10:20.354 --> 10:21.822
Bro, you had one job.

10:21.822 --> 10:23.457
- I-I mean, it's similar enough.
- [Bear] Yeah,

10:23.457 --> 10:24.692
yeah, don't worry. It's
all still the same plan.

10:24.692 --> 10:26.694
- Fuck it.
- All right, so this is the plan.

10:26.694 --> 10:28.195
♪ ♪

10:28.195 --> 10:29.597
<i>White Steve and Bone Thug Dog,</i>

10:29.597 --> 10:31.265
<i>go to the front desk
and tell them</i>

10:31.265 --> 10:32.766
<i>that you have a tour
with the manager.</i>

10:32.766 --> 10:34.201
This is stupid.
They're never gonna believe us.

10:34.201 --> 10:36.303
- Your face is stupid.
- [sighs]

10:36.303 --> 10:38.639
- Yeah.
- [Bear] <i>No matter what happens,</i>

10:38.639 --> 10:40.341
<i>make sure they give you guys
that tour,</i>

10:40.341 --> 10:42.476
<i>'cause that will be
the distraction.</i>

10:42.476 --> 10:44.245
<i>Jackie and Elora,
y'all are gonna go in there</i>

10:44.245 --> 10:45.746
<i>and cut the phone lines,
all right?</i>

10:45.746 --> 10:48.182
I don't know what a phone line
looks like.

10:48.182 --> 10:50.417
- Do you?
- Fuck no.

10:50.417 --> 10:52.386
I know what it looks like.

10:52.386 --> 10:54.221
[Ansel]
I don't.

10:54.221 --> 10:56.122
I'll take that.

10:58.225 --> 10:59.360
Cheese.

10:59.360 --> 11:00.527
- What?
- Buddy, you know

11:00.527 --> 11:02.096
how to spot a phone line, right?

11:02.096 --> 11:03.631
Of course. I-I'm a gamer.

11:03.631 --> 11:05.499
- I-I know cables.
- He knows cables.

11:05.499 --> 11:07.434
- [cheering]
- He's a gamer.
All right, awesome.

11:07.434 --> 11:08.769
All right, so,
Cheese will go with y'all.

11:08.769 --> 11:11.037
♪ ♪

11:13.140 --> 11:15.109
<i>Uh, Weeze, you go in the front</i>

11:15.109 --> 11:17.177
<i>and keep
the security guard busy.</i>

11:17.177 --> 11:19.513
<i>And if you see the cops,
scream as loud as you can</i>

11:19.513 --> 11:21.682
<i>- and run back to the bus.</i>
- [Weeze] <i>Wait,</i>

11:21.682 --> 11:23.350
why do I scream?

11:23.350 --> 11:25.152
I mean,
'cause you got to alert us.

11:25.152 --> 11:27.087
- Like, right? Like...
- Y... Right.

11:27.087 --> 11:28.389
- Yeah, just alert us, bro.
- Alert us.

11:28.389 --> 11:30.490
How do you want me to scream?

11:31.325 --> 11:33.127
- Like, just, like,
really fucking loud.
- Wh...

11:33.127 --> 11:34.428
<i>♪ Yeah, ah-ah... ♪</i>

11:34.428 --> 11:35.763
Ah!

11:35.763 --> 11:37.798
- Like that.
- Like that.

11:37.798 --> 11:39.500
What if you guys are somewhere
you can't hear me?

11:39.500 --> 11:41.335
That's a good point. I mean...

11:41.335 --> 11:43.237
- [Jackie] That's true.
- [Bear] That's a good point.

11:43.237 --> 11:44.705
You could text us
in the group chat?

11:44.705 --> 11:47.341
- [Bear] Ooh.
- Word. That's better.

11:47.341 --> 11:49.643
You're right.
I'll use exclamation points.

11:49.643 --> 11:51.345
♪ ♪

11:51.345 --> 11:53.380
[Bear]
<i>All right, me and Willie Jack--</i>

11:53.380 --> 11:54.782
Oh, "Willie Jack and I."

11:54.782 --> 11:56.650
What?

11:56.650 --> 11:58.451
He's right.

12:00.153 --> 12:02.656
[sighs]
Willie Jack and I--

12:02.656 --> 12:04.391
<i>we'll find Chibon's room...</i>

12:04.391 --> 12:05.392
Let's do it.

12:05.392 --> 12:06.427
<i>...boom, grab him</i>

12:06.427 --> 12:08.128
<i>and get out of there.</i>

12:08.128 --> 12:09.496
All right?

12:09.496 --> 12:11.431
- [laughs] Yes.
- What's he even look like?

12:12.766 --> 12:15.202
- You know what
he looks like, right?
- Fuck no.

12:15.202 --> 12:17.538
- Don't know what he looks like?
- [Willie Jack] No,
not even, bro.

12:17.538 --> 12:19.273
What do you mean you don't know
what he looks like?

12:19.273 --> 12:22.076
He doesn't have Facebook.
Fuck I look like, FBI? Fuck.

12:22.076 --> 12:24.211
Some Indian guy, I suppose.

12:24.211 --> 12:26.447
What if he doesn't want to go?

12:26.447 --> 12:28.282
Hmm.

12:28.282 --> 12:30.717
Well, shit, I didn't
fuckin' think about that.

12:32.319 --> 12:34.088
Oh, man...

12:34.088 --> 12:36.523
H-He'll want to go.

12:36.523 --> 12:38.692
- He's gonna want to leave.
- He's gonna want to get
out of there.

12:38.692 --> 12:41.462
- Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.
- [Bear] He's gonna want
to get out of here.

12:41.462 --> 12:43.364
[Bear]
All right? Okay, all right.

12:43.364 --> 12:45.232
We got this shit.
We're the fucking Rez Dogs.

12:45.232 --> 12:47.668
- Fuck yeah. Rose gold.
- [White Steve] Wait-wait
a minute.

12:47.668 --> 12:49.503
Yeah, we ain't no Rez Dogs.

12:49.503 --> 12:52.039
Yeah, man,
we're the Bad Guy Gang.

12:52.039 --> 12:54.441
- [scoffs] NDN Mafia, bitch.
- Yeah.

12:55.475 --> 12:56.676
Well...

12:58.679 --> 13:00.481
...do you guys want to join?

13:00.481 --> 13:02.782
We can all be Rez Dogs.

13:07.721 --> 13:09.223
Bet.

13:09.223 --> 13:10.457
Yeah?

13:10.457 --> 13:12.226
Fucking Rez Dogs.

13:12.226 --> 13:13.661
[all]
Fucking Rez Dogs.

13:13.661 --> 13:15.529
[cheering, hooting]

13:20.133 --> 13:22.102
Hold-hold up.

13:22.102 --> 13:24.438
Slow your roll.

13:24.438 --> 13:27.107
What are we, chicken livers?

13:27.107 --> 13:28.542
What's our job?

13:28.542 --> 13:30.210
You got the best job.

13:30.210 --> 13:32.246
Yeah, you guys just-just
chill in the bus and wait.

13:32.246 --> 13:34.348
[Elora]
Be ready to drive away fast.

13:34.348 --> 13:36.116
[Cheese]
Yeah, m-moderately fast.

13:36.116 --> 13:38.719
- [Bear] Yeah.
- Getaway drivers?

13:38.719 --> 13:41.755
Yeah, I-I... I don't know
if you guys should come in.

13:41.755 --> 13:45.125
- Why?
- Why?

13:46.326 --> 13:47.661
Well, 'cause...

13:47.661 --> 13:49.296
'Cause you look
half crazy, fuck.

13:49.296 --> 13:50.997
They're just gonna keep you
in there, shit.

13:52.199 --> 13:54.101
Uh, plus, we don't
have a CDL license.

13:54.101 --> 13:56.470
- Yeah, we only got
our Rez license.
- [Willie Jack] Yeah.

13:56.470 --> 13:58.339
- Ninety down the back roads.
- [Cheese clears throat]

13:58.339 --> 14:00.674
Getaway drivers.

14:00.674 --> 14:02.376
Can you believe it?

14:02.376 --> 14:04.712
Yeah.

14:04.712 --> 14:07.314
- All right, well, Rez Dogs.
- [cheering, hooting]

14:09.549 --> 14:11.318
Yay! Yay! Yay! Yay!

14:17.821 --> 14:18.342
What are you doing?

14:18.342 --> 14:19.477
- You first.
- Why me?

14:19.477 --> 14:20.911
- You're white.
- Fuck.

14:26.383 --> 14:27.451
Hi.

14:27.451 --> 14:29.320
Can I help you?

14:29.320 --> 14:30.488
Yes, actually.

14:30.488 --> 14:33.224
I am Mr. White.

14:33.224 --> 14:35.559
And this is...

14:35.559 --> 14:37.294
Mr. Br--

14:37.294 --> 14:38.496
[quietly] Don't say Brown.

14:38.496 --> 14:40.965
Mr. Dog.

14:40.965 --> 14:43.968
Mr. White and Mr. Dog.

14:43.968 --> 14:46.070
What can I do for you?

14:46.070 --> 14:48.039
Uh, yes, I'm glad you asked.

14:48.039 --> 14:51.309
- Mm.
- We have an appointment
with management

14:51.309 --> 14:53.811
to do a walk-around.

14:53.811 --> 14:55.813
A walk-around?

14:55.813 --> 14:58.049
- [whispers] A tour.
- A-A tour,

14:58.049 --> 14:59.550
with management.

14:59.550 --> 15:02.420
We're writing an article
for an assignment.

15:02.420 --> 15:04.288
Tour with management.

15:04.288 --> 15:06.023
And you have an appointment?

15:06.023 --> 15:07.524
Yes.

15:12.262 --> 15:13.797
Let's do it.

15:16.967 --> 15:19.470
Um... Hey, do you know anything

15:19.470 --> 15:21.872
about a walk-around
scheduled for today?

15:24.608 --> 15:27.144
I don't...
[sighs]

15:27.144 --> 15:29.313
Yeah, I'm not seeing anything.

15:29.313 --> 15:31.082
What exactly
were you wanting to do?

15:31.082 --> 15:33.951
Um, a "toure" for the paper.

15:33.951 --> 15:36.286
Like I said, it's, uh,
for an article.

15:37.254 --> 15:38.956
And do you have a card?

15:38.956 --> 15:41.024
[short chuckle]
I'm glad you asked.

15:43.327 --> 15:45.229
Uh, I do not have one.

15:45.229 --> 15:47.331
Okay.

15:52.403 --> 15:55.272
This is, um, handwritten.

15:56.273 --> 15:59.042
Sorry, I ran out of the usual.

16:02.579 --> 16:05.148
♪ ♪

16:09.253 --> 16:11.922
- [indistinct chatter]
- Oh, shit.

16:11.922 --> 16:13.791
[whispers]
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

16:13.791 --> 16:15.325
Go.

16:17.861 --> 16:19.196
Check that shit.

16:20.330 --> 16:21.898
Smith.

16:23.267 --> 16:24.969
Sheridan. The fuck?

16:24.969 --> 16:26.804
Johnson.

16:26.804 --> 16:29.206
Johns... w-where the-where
the fuck are all the Indians at?

16:29.206 --> 16:30.941
[blows raspberry]

16:30.941 --> 16:32.877
<i>♪ See you ain't slow... ♪</i>

16:32.877 --> 16:35.179
- [Bear] I'm... That's it.
- Are you sure?

16:35.179 --> 16:37.348
- Yeah.
- What if it blows
the building up?

16:37.348 --> 16:38.883
It's not a bomb.

16:38.883 --> 16:40.284
What if I get electrocuted?

16:43.854 --> 16:45.889
♪ ♪

16:47.991 --> 16:50.795
I can, uh, call management.

16:50.795 --> 16:53.364
- They're not on-site, but...
- Okay.

16:53.364 --> 16:54.899
Send it.

16:54.899 --> 16:57.034
Just send that shit, bro.

16:59.069 --> 17:01.238
That's weird.
The phones are down again.

17:01.238 --> 17:03.574
Okay, I can give you
a quick tour,

17:03.574 --> 17:06.811
but just get what you need
and then you should probably go.

17:06.811 --> 17:08.012
- Perfect.
- Bet.

17:08.012 --> 17:09.246
Come on.

17:12.516 --> 17:15.019
- See? Nothing to worry about.
- [laughs softly]

17:15.019 --> 17:16.554
[Willie Jack]
Oh, fuck, bro.

17:16.554 --> 17:18.823
- What's up?
- This one says Fixico.

17:18.823 --> 17:20.825
- Maxi...
- Oh, yeah?

17:20.825 --> 17:22.192
"Maximoose"?

17:25.129 --> 17:27.098
No, fuck that. It's not him.

17:27.098 --> 17:29.834
Hey, did you say Maximus?

17:29.834 --> 17:31.836
Yeah, bro. Keep looking.

17:31.836 --> 17:34.372
Bro. This is him.

17:34.372 --> 17:35.906
What?

17:36.940 --> 17:38.442
Yo, this is him, man.

17:47.251 --> 17:50.487
- [Chatter in distance]
- [phones ringing in distance]

17:52.823 --> 17:54.024
Maximus.

17:55.993 --> 17:58.895
It's, uh... It's me, Bear.

17:59.997 --> 18:02.366
I... I don't know
if you remember me,

18:02.366 --> 18:05.369
- but we, uh--
- I know who the fuck you are.

18:05.369 --> 18:07.138
What are you doing here?

18:07.138 --> 18:09.140
Oh. Um...

18:09.140 --> 18:11.242
Well, we-we came to, uh...

18:11.242 --> 18:13.176
We came because of Fixico.

18:14.144 --> 18:16.347
Fixico? I just... I...

18:16.347 --> 18:18.282
I'm Fixico.

18:19.350 --> 18:21.052
Old Man Fixico?

18:21.052 --> 18:23.387
- [Bear] Do you know
his first name?
- Fuck no.

18:23.387 --> 18:26.423
Uh, Old Man Fixico,
your cousin-brother?

18:27.424 --> 18:29.393
Oh, him.

18:29.393 --> 18:31.395
What the hell does he want?

18:31.395 --> 18:34.832
Um, he's...

18:34.832 --> 18:36.467
he's not doing too good.

18:36.467 --> 18:39.870
It's bad. Like, really bad.

18:39.870 --> 18:41.339
Hmm.

18:41.339 --> 18:43.474
[Bear]
Yeah, we, uh...

18:43.474 --> 18:45.376
That's why we're here.

18:45.376 --> 18:47.210
We're trying to break you out.

18:48.245 --> 18:49.947
[chuckles]

18:49.947 --> 18:52.216
Break me out?

18:52.216 --> 18:54.085
Yeah, you know, like, jailbreak?

18:54.085 --> 18:56.954
[laughs]

18:56.954 --> 19:00.858
You stupid bastard, you don't
have to break me out of here.

19:00.858 --> 19:02.960
[Bear]
What do you mean?

19:02.960 --> 19:06.464
I-I can leave
any time I want. I...

19:06.464 --> 19:09.266
I'm staying 'cause I need to.

19:09.266 --> 19:11.535
I... They came and took you.

19:11.535 --> 19:13.104
Oh, that happens
every six months or so.

19:13.104 --> 19:16.107
I get off my meds,
I get a little crazy,

19:16.107 --> 19:18.075
I start writing letters
to people--

19:18.075 --> 19:19.810
- the city, the mayor,
- Oh...

19:19.810 --> 19:22.213
the librarian--

19:22.213 --> 19:24.782
they find out about it,
they come and get me

19:24.782 --> 19:26.784
and take me back,
I get back on my meds,

19:26.784 --> 19:30.488
I stabilize until I, uh...

19:30.488 --> 19:33.858
I forget to take them again.

19:33.858 --> 19:36.193
So you're choosing to be here?

19:37.227 --> 19:38.462
Well, duh.

19:38.462 --> 19:40.064
What? I get liver and onions,

19:40.064 --> 19:42.833
I got good air conditioning,
heating, uh...

19:42.833 --> 19:45.002
It's like a paid holiday. Yeah.

19:45.002 --> 19:47.271
Oh, fuck.

19:47.271 --> 19:49.940
I haven't, uh...

19:49.940 --> 19:53.210
talked to my cousin
in a long time.

19:53.210 --> 19:56.347
Well, you should put all that
bad shit behind you guys now,

19:56.347 --> 19:59.250
'cause he's not gonna
be here much longer.

19:59.250 --> 20:00.951
Eh.

20:13.897 --> 20:17.868
You know, all you elders--
you got robbed of your feelings

20:17.868 --> 20:20.971
and now you can't even admit
or express them anymore.

20:20.971 --> 20:24.207
So you just sit here in your
room and stare out the window.

20:25.509 --> 20:27.912
Like, I'm sorry,
whatever you went through--

20:27.912 --> 20:30.481
boarding school, abuse--
whatever happened to you,

20:30.481 --> 20:32.350
I-I get it, but...

20:32.350 --> 20:34.852
us young people--
we know things, too.

20:34.852 --> 20:36.453
[scoffs]

20:38.956 --> 20:40.358
[sniffles]

20:40.358 --> 20:44.227
I'd give anything
to see my cousin Daniel again.

20:48.265 --> 20:50.501
Fixico wants to see you
and you're just in here,

20:50.501 --> 20:52.970
fucking acting all stubborn?

20:52.970 --> 20:55.106
Fucking go, bro.

20:55.106 --> 20:56.940
Fuck it. We tried.

20:58.208 --> 21:00.077
I'll go.

21:04.515 --> 21:07.051
Well, don't just stand there
like a couple of dummies.

21:07.051 --> 21:08.219
I said I'd go.

21:08.219 --> 21:10.354
Let's go.

21:10.354 --> 21:12.322
Grab my coat.

21:16.126 --> 21:18.996
<i>♪ One, o-one... ♪</i>

21:18.996 --> 21:20.865
There's so many bathrooms here.

21:20.865 --> 21:22.800
I didn't know
that there'd be so many...

21:22.800 --> 21:24.502
Uh, actually, can we go back?
I think I missed some things.

21:24.502 --> 21:26.337
Bro, it's okay.
It's all good.

21:26.337 --> 21:28.205
Mr. Fixico, you checking out?

21:28.205 --> 21:31.509
Uh, yeah. Yes, Ann,
I believe I will.

21:31.509 --> 21:33.311
How long
you leaving us for today?

21:33.311 --> 21:35.813
Uh...

21:35.813 --> 21:38.049
- I don't know.
- [laughs] Okay.

21:38.049 --> 21:40.051
Well, you know what to do.

21:40.051 --> 21:41.786
Okay.

21:41.786 --> 21:43.120
Thank you, Annie.

21:43.120 --> 21:46.090
[Bear]
Oh, wait, wait, there. Um...

21:46.090 --> 21:49.226
Our friends think
we're busting you out,

21:49.226 --> 21:53.030
and, um...
can we act like we did?

21:56.166 --> 21:57.335
[chuckles]

21:57.335 --> 21:59.203
♪ ♪

21:59.203 --> 22:01.238
- Holy fuck, they did it.
- [Maximus] Where's my stuff?

22:01.238 --> 22:03.274
- [Bear] Fuck you guys.
- [Willie Jack laughs]

22:03.274 --> 22:05.343
[Maximus]
What-what the hell
are you trying to do?

22:05.343 --> 22:07.044
[Willie Jack imitates gunshots]

22:07.044 --> 22:08.478
Release the anchor.

22:10.481 --> 22:12.216
The fuck you talking about?

22:12.216 --> 22:13.517
What? It's the truth.

22:13.517 --> 22:15.752
We went to the hospital
to go get Uncle.

22:16.820 --> 22:18.422
So, what about the bus, then?

22:20.391 --> 22:22.360
What about it?

22:22.360 --> 22:23.995
♪ ♪

22:23.995 --> 22:25.963
Hey, you guys were amazing.

22:25.963 --> 22:28.332
I... I'm proud of you.

22:28.332 --> 22:30.001
And you were right.

22:30.001 --> 22:32.837
Getaway driver is pretty great.

22:32.837 --> 22:35.272
- [loud pop]
- Oh, shit.

22:35.272 --> 22:37.975
- Smoke signals. Not good.
- Oh, fuck, bro! Smoke!

22:37.975 --> 22:40.811
This little lady's
going to meet her creator.

22:40.811 --> 22:44.081
- [all clamoring]
- Everyone off.

22:44.081 --> 22:46.050
Let's go!
[Ansel] Go, go, go, go, go, go!

22:46.050 --> 22:47.985
- Go, go, go!
- Ah!

22:47.985 --> 22:49.086
Oh, shit! Oh...

22:49.086 --> 22:50.454
Keep going--

22:50.454 --> 22:53.190
[all exclaim]

22:57.995 --> 23:00.398
- God...
- Ah.

23:00.398 --> 23:01.866
♪ ♪

23:01.866 --> 23:03.868
Holy... holy shit.

23:03.868 --> 23:05.469
[Willie Jack]
Man, fuck that.

23:05.469 --> 23:07.805
- Whoa.
- All right, let's kick rocks.

23:07.805 --> 23:09.807
Split up. Split up.

23:09.807 --> 23:12.810
- Find shelter.
- Go, go, go. Anywhere, Ansel.

23:12.810 --> 23:14.211
[Bear]
Come on, let's go, let's go.

23:14.211 --> 23:17.348
Just not with me.

23:17.348 --> 23:19.784
<i>Listen, why are you doing this?</i>

23:19.784 --> 23:23.254
You can just walk away.

23:23.254 --> 23:25.122
After all we've been through.

23:25.122 --> 23:27.458
Tired of the crimes you all do.

23:27.458 --> 23:30.061
Time to clean these streets up.

23:30.061 --> 23:31.094
Crime.

23:32.262 --> 23:34.932
- What even is crime?
- Well, specifically,

23:34.932 --> 23:36.801
it's a misdemeanor crime.

23:36.801 --> 23:39.903
You're all getting tickets.
Got witness.

23:41.038 --> 23:43.274
No.

23:43.274 --> 23:44.909
You're not gonna do that.

23:44.909 --> 23:46.177
Fuck I ain't.

23:46.177 --> 23:49.213
They were taking care
of an elder.

23:49.213 --> 23:51.215
I can't let you.

23:51.215 --> 23:53.784
What the fuck you gonna do,
Kenny Boy?

23:56.153 --> 23:57.354
It was me.

23:59.356 --> 24:00.992
It was all me.

24:00.992 --> 24:02.493
Fuck you mean?

24:02.493 --> 24:03.961
The kids weren't even there.

24:05.029 --> 24:07.464
It was just me.

24:08.966 --> 24:10.167
And him.

24:12.136 --> 24:15.806
- Me?
- Kenny Boy, don't do this.

24:15.806 --> 24:17.942
They need to pay
for their crimes, too.

24:17.942 --> 24:19.309
Brother...

24:20.944 --> 24:22.913
...and you are my brother--

24:22.913 --> 24:25.082
I can't let these kids
take the heat.

24:25.082 --> 24:27.184
They're good kids.

24:28.218 --> 24:29.854
'Cause that's what we do.

24:29.854 --> 24:32.223
["East October" by John Moreland
playing]

24:32.223 --> 24:34.091
<i>We show up for each other.</i>

24:35.392 --> 24:37.060
<i>We're a community.</i>

24:38.295 --> 24:40.063
<i>You know that.</i>

24:41.265 --> 24:43.067
<i>Some we like,</i>

24:43.067 --> 24:45.870
<i>some we don't.</i>

24:45.870 --> 24:48.272
<i>Some borrow money.</i>

24:48.272 --> 24:50.007
<i>A lot.</i>

24:50.007 --> 24:52.209
<i>♪ Like send-ups... ♪</i>

24:52.209 --> 24:54.445
<i>We hold each other accountable.</i>

24:54.445 --> 24:56.447
<i>♪ We were children... ♪</i>

24:56.447 --> 24:58.916
<i>And sometimes
we take the heat.</i>

24:58.916 --> 25:01.085
<i>♪ Dressed up like men... ♪</i>

25:01.085 --> 25:03.821
<i>But it's all in service
of each other.</i>

25:03.821 --> 25:05.923
<i>♪ Places we'd never been... ♪</i>

25:05.923 --> 25:07.958
<i>All of us.</i>

25:09.860 --> 25:12.463
<i>♪ How am I ever gonna get by? ♪</i>

25:12.463 --> 25:17.334
<i>♪ How am I ever gonna get by
all by myself? ♪</i>

25:26.010 --> 25:29.279
<i>[exhales sharply]
All of us.</i>

25:31.982 --> 25:35.452
And Big,
I've been sober since the woods.

25:37.855 --> 25:40.757
Ah.
Been through a lot, Kenny Boy.

25:41.525 --> 25:43.193
Aho.

25:44.161 --> 25:46.196
♪ ♪

26:14.491 --> 26:16.493
♪ ♪

26:19.530 --> 26:21.799
[Big sighs]

26:21.799 --> 26:24.334
Go ahead.
Push that space bar to play it.

26:26.537 --> 26:28.839
The fuck is this?

26:28.839 --> 26:31.542
What? Shit.

26:31.542 --> 26:34.144
Quit looking at that.
What's wrong with you?

26:37.381 --> 26:38.849
[Willie Jack]
<i>Come on, skoden.</i>

26:38.849 --> 26:39.917
[Big]
Uh-huh.

26:39.917 --> 26:42.219
Got this sent on Facebooks.

26:42.219 --> 26:44.822
Caught you red-handed.

26:44.822 --> 26:47.124
<i>- [Willie Jack imitates gunshots]</i>
- T-This is a deepfake.

26:47.124 --> 26:48.492
That's not us.

26:48.492 --> 26:50.494
Criminals have
their faces covered.

26:50.494 --> 26:52.830
[Big]
You're gonna talk to me.
You hear me?

26:52.830 --> 26:55.499
[Willie Jack]
<i>The fuck? What the fuck? Shit.</i>

26:55.499 --> 26:57.835
That's not me, fuck.

26:57.835 --> 26:59.870
Got the wrong guy.

26:59.870 --> 27:01.372
<i>[imitates gunshots]</i>

27:01.372 --> 27:02.806
<i>Oh, fuck.</i>

27:05.342 --> 27:07.344
♪ ♪

27:26.130 --> 27:28.932
